.TH _printf
.SH NAME
\fB_printf\fP 
.SH SYNOPSIS
_printf ("FORMAT",[ARGUMENT]);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The format consists of regular text and format specifiers, which are placeholders for
arguments to be printed. Format specifiers are preceded by the `%` character, and
each specifier is replaced by the value of the corresponding argument.

    The following format specifiers are supported:
    %d   Print an integer.
    %i   Print an integer
    %c   Print a character.
    %s   Print a string.
    %%   Displays a literal percentage (`%`).
    
.SH RETURN VALUE
When the operation completes successfully, _printf returns the number of characters written. Otherwise,
a negative number is returned to indicate an error.

.SH EXAMPLES
Usage :

    Formatting an integer:
       _printf("The concert starts in %d minute\n", 20)
       
    Formatting a character:
       _printf("Displays a character: %c\n", "A")
       
    Formatting a string:
       _printf("%s\n", "This is our first project")
       
